TITLE: LGBTQ small business owners struggle to find financing
SUMMARY: LGBTQ-owned businesses reported more rejections than non-LGBTQ businesses that applied for funding, according to a 2022 report.

TITLE: Key Fed inflation measure shows prices rose just 0.3% in May
SUMMARY: The personal consumption expenditures price index excluding food and energy was expected to increase 0.3% in May and 4.7% from a year ago.

TITLE: First-quarter economic growth was actually 2%, up from 1.3% first reported in major GDP revision
SUMMARY: The U.S. economy showed much stronger-than-expected growth in the first quarter than previously thought.

SUMMARY: The U.S. will enter a downturn in the fourth quarter, followed by a "year of contraction and a European recession in 2024," according to HSBC Asset Management.

SUMMARY: Major central banks will have to hold rates high for much longer than some investors expect, the IMF's Gita Gopinath told CNBC Tuesday.

TITLE: Corporate bankruptcies and defaults are surging – here's why
SUMMARY: The corporate default rate is up and rising as interest rates remain elevated, making it more expensive for companies to refinance debt.

SUMMARY: S&P Global's Chris Williamson described the numbers as "worrying" as the euro zone's flash composite PMI dropped to 50.3 in June.

SUMMARY: The Bank of England is "caught between a rock and a hard place" as it prepares for a key monetary policy decision.

SUMMARY: Economic freedom has been more elusive for Black people. Veteran portfolio manager Jim Casselberry is trying to do something about that.

SUMMARY: Major central banks are taking very different approaches to monetary policy, as the global economy "is no longer synchronized," an expert said.

TITLE: Inflation rose at a 4% annual rate in May, the lowest in 2 years
SUMMARY: The consumer price index was expected to rise 0.1% in May, according to the Dow Jones consensus estimate.

SUMMARY: The euro zone entered a recession in the first quarter of this year and economists are not optimistic for the coming months.

SUMMARY: Nonfarm payrolls were expected to increase by 190,000 in May, according to Dow Jones.

SUMMARY: The core personal consumption expenditures price index was expected to increase 0.3% in April, according to a Dow Jones estimate.

SUMMARY: Whether it's personalized shopping or self-driving cars, AI will become a factor in virtually everyone's lives.
